N:debugging
D:Debug code, runtime behavior, regressions, flaky failures, and code-adjacent incidents with a systematic reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → verify loop. Use after symptom triage when the user needs a debugging workflow, not just log line selection.
G:debugging regression-isolation reproduction flaky-tests git-bisect root-cause
U[6]:
  Runtime bugs, regressions, or incorrect behavior with a narrowed suspect boundary
  Flaky or intermittent failures that need reproduction and stabilization
  CI/test failures after the first actionable error is already known
  Frontend/backend/fullstack bugs that need recent-change or config comparison
  Requests to reproduce, isolate, bisect, fix, or verify a bug
  Debugging plans that should route raw log triage to log-analysis first
S[7]{n,action}:
  1,Frame the failure precisely
  2,Build the smallest reliable reproduction
  3,Isolate the failing boundary
  4,Form hypotheses and run the smallest discriminating check
  5,Handle common debugging modes explicitly
  6,Fix the cause then prove it
  7,Escalate carefully when evidence is weak
